The paper deals with privacy-preserving ride-sharing organization, which involves encryption and similarity measurement of trip data. This suggests that the paper may belong to the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes two schemes for ride-sharing, which involves dividing the ride-sharing area into cells and using algorithms to optimize the ride-sharing process. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of data structures (cs.DS), databases (cs.DB), machine learning (cs.LG), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
